@node High-Level Overview
@section High-Level Overview

Xeetapus follows a traditional client-server architecture.  The client
is a single-page application written in React, while the server is a
custom HTTP server written in Zig.  The two communicate exclusively
through a RESTful JSON API.

The system consists of three main layers:

@enumerate
@item
The frontend, which runs in the user's web browser and provides the
user interface.

@item
The backend HTTP server, which handles client requests, enforces
security policies, and manages application logic.

@item
The database, which provides persistent storage for all application
data.
@end enumerate

